# Shopping Cart App (CSS)

Welcome to the Shopping Cart App, a beginner-friendly project focused on mastering HTML and CSS for e-commerce interfaces. This experiment demonstrates how to build a visually appealing and functional shopping cart using only HTML and CSS.

## Features
- Responsive shopping cart layout
- Product listing with images
- Add/remove items visually (UI only)
- Clean, modern design

## Folder Structure
- `images/`: Contains product and logo images for the app
- `public/css/`: CSS stylesheets for layout and design
- `public/html/`: HTML files for the shopping cart pages

## How to Use
1. Open any HTML file in the `public/html/` folder with your browser.
2. Explore the cart interface and product listings.
3. Modify the CSS in `public/css/` to experiment with styles.

## Learning Outcomes
- Practice semantic HTML structure
- Master CSS layouts and responsive design
- Understand the basics of e-commerce UI/UX

